Description: This is a one-of-a-kind guitar that was professionally assembled by Don’t Panic Guitar Works out of Lewiston, Pennsylvania. It is a custom build that has every bit of the twang you would expect from a classic Fender Telecaster. It’s used but still in mint condition. -Chrome hardware including a custom six saddle string thru bridge -Mighty Mite Solid Maple Neck with skunk stripe finished in a vintage tint nitro gloss -Premium Kluson Locking Tuners - Keep great tune - very cool vintage style buttons -White Graph Tech Tusq String Trees -Custom 3 ply white armrest guard -Fatboy Telecaster Neck Pickup -Surf 90 Bridge Pickup These pickups are boutique and sound amazing. The Bridge is very similar to the tone of a traditional Tele bridge with a bit more power, growl, and sparkle, like a gretsch, a dearmond, and p90 had a baby! Awesome! The Neck Fatboy is fat and beefy but very clear and articulate, similar to my ears to a Fat 50s strat pup and great for blues. The middle position is a great blend of the two. It sounds amazing. This guitar would be great for country, blues, classic rock, punk, and alt rock.  Setup with medium-low action to my preference. A pro setup may be required as with any new-to-YOU guitar. The guitar will ship in basic padded gig bag with substantial packaging to ensure safe arrival.
Title: Custom Built Telecaster - Gun Metal Blue with Incredible TWANG
